Two men have been seriously injured in a disturbance in Glasgow city centre.
Police said about eight people were involved in an incident outside the BHS store on Sauchiehall Street at about 03:14 on Sunday.
Two men, aged 32 and 28, were treated for injuries at Glasgow Royal Infirmary.
Detectives are examining CCTV and said the area would have been busy at the time with pedestrians. They have appealed for witnesses to come forward.

